OL,5,Cwoman
OL,7,F"We turned up at reception, we had to
OL,8,Fqueue. It was very busy, very
OL,9,Fchaotic," she said.
OL,11,FMrs Ward said she voiced concerns that
OL,12,FSophie may have meningitis at each
OL,13,Fstage of their hospital visit, but was
OL,14,Fassured she could go home.
OL,16,FShe said: "I think she was treated in
OL,17,Fa very sloppy, unprofessional manner
OL,18,Fthat didn't look at the patient in
OL,19,Ffront of them, (and) had almost a
OL,20,Fforegone conclusion that this was not
OL,21,Fmeningitis."
